name: the little prince and the crow

metadata.name: the little prince and the crow
metadata.description:
-the little prince and the crow-


welcome, my dear spectator..

today's tale is that of a little prince and a crow..

better keep those eyes open..


are you still there, my dear spectator ?


i'd trade you my cape for your feathers.
i'd trade you my army for your talons.
i'd trade you my title for your wisdom.
i'd trade you my crown for your wings.


what good are feathers if it's on clipped wings...
what good is an army if it can be sold...
what good is a title if it signifies nothing...
what good is a crown if it is bent...


i'd trade you nothing... for nothing is the currency of many.

i know what will be... i am one of many... 
yet few have stood before a prince who had nothing to offer.


so what did we learn, my little spectator ?
